Text: Hello, How am I, I am keeping well thank you. My name is Andy Wyatt.
How old am I, I am in my 80s now. I am a bit forgetful.

Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today, is because I have come for a routine eye routine eye exam today. I'm not having any particular problems with my eyes but my glasses are a bit scratched. That is what brings me along today, this is why I am here, this is what brought me along, I am here, my because I want a routine eye check up and because my glasses are scratched.

My current glasses are varifocals, which I wear all the time, they are about 2 years old, if my memory serves me correctly. My vision is pretty good at all distances, in the distance and for reading my vision is good, when I use my glasses. My last sight test was a year ago I think. I didn't get my glasses updated at my last eye examination because my prescription hadn't changed so my glasses are 2 years old. The lenses in my glasses are a little scratched and the frames are now a bit tattered. I keep dropping my glasses they slip down my nose and are on the floor before I know it.

I don't have any problems with my eyes or vision at all. I'm not experiencing any headaches, eyestrain or double vision. I don't get any (flashes) flashing lights. The only thing I've noticed is the occasional floater in both my eyes that I've had for the past year now.

I've never been to the hospital for my eyes, nor have I had to see a doctor about my eyes, but at my last eye test I was told that I have early signs of age-related macular degeneration as well as mild cataracts. I haven't had any injuries, accidents or operations on my eyes. I don't recall having my eyes patched as a child. I use eye drops for my eyes whenever they feel dry, which can happen most evenings. I think the eye drops are called hyprormellose or something like that.Sometimes my eyes get quite watery, particularly if I'm outside.
My family don't have any eye or health problems, like diabetes or high blood pressure, as far as I'm aware. Ahh, I almost forgot, my mum had cataract surgery a couple years back.

My general health is okay apart from high cholesterol, for which I take Statins. I also get my blood checked 2 times a year. My doctor is a bit over the top like that. I have no allergies and I don't smoke. The only medication I take are statins for my cholesterol. I don't have diabetes.

I wear my glasses for driving when I'm heading to participate in community volunteering which I'm really passionate about! I'm a volunteer driver, helping people get to their appointments if they can't get there themselves, mostly its hospital trips these days! I don't have a job because I am retired now. I like to keep myself busy with my grandchildren and from time to time I dabble in photography. I really hate using screens. I don't have a mobile phone and I don't have much need for a computer so I almost never use the one at home my son bought me. Occasionally I might spend a few minutes using the computer during the week but no more than that.
I do not have anything else to add. I have nothing more to tell you.
